Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *Software Engineer* role with *PowerSchool*. I bring more than three years of experience building backend systems, AI-driven workflows, and data-heavy services, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University. The mix of *AWS serverless*, *Python*, *TypeScript*, *SQL*, and production debugging in this role closely matches the systems I have been building.

At Sperse, I built a *multi-tenant* CRM orchestration layer in *Python* and *FastAPI* that routes requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents with tenant-aware access control, production monitoring, and secure tool execution for 10,000+ users. I also built a *TypeScript* and *React Flow* workflow builder for durable, resumable automations using *Temporal*, an agentic code review pipeline that integrates *OpenAI Codex* with a custom *Bitbucket MCP* server, and a *FastMCP* server exposing 160+ backend actions with *Pydantic* validation and *OpenTelemetry* instrumentation. At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service with *Java*, *Spring Boot*, *PostgreSQL*, and *Redis*, optimized *SQL* and PostgreSQL query paths for reporting-style access, and orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions* and *AWS Lambda* across 100K+ weekly executions. That combination of cloud-native backend work, AI-assisted automation, and operational rigor is the experience I would bring to PowerSchool's reporting and data platform work.

PowerSchool's mission to empower educators, administrators, and families to help students learn in a way that is right for them aligns with how I think about engineering. I am especially drawn to the emphasis on *support every step*, *make personalization possible*, and *work together* through data. I would welcome the opportunity to contribute to the technical depth, collaboration, and engineering discipline this team values, and to help build systems that make student-facing experiences more reliable and more personalized.

I would be glad to discuss how my background maps to your team's priorities. You can reach me at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

